Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Gray-Code Method", "TechNoteSection",
 CellID->35322904,ExpressionUUID->"93f84cb8-f391-4959-a144-ff23ae5086a6"],

Cell["\<\
We first discuss one systematic method based on the Gray code to decompose a \
multi- control unitary gate into factors of either controlled-unitary or CNOT \
gates. \
\>", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->2098065290,ExpressionUUID->"479a6c66-9a19-403a-b039-ff18c9a39328"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "For example, consider a 3-control unitary gate as shown in the quantum \
circuit in Figure 2 below, where ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["V", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "06e84959-3b28-4a86-b63d-89efcbc909dc"],
 " is another unitary operator such that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["V", "4"], "=", "U"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "8346f5c0-0f7d-433e-a438-4276b8a72748"],
 ". When every control qubit is set to |1\:27e9, all ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["V", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "25e23f7d-b453-4a4a-b2c9-2d998eecb729"],
 " gates in the diagram operate on the target qubit while the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["V", "\[Dagger]"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "7025f826-5449-4540-8aaa-cd5d216a29e0"],
 " gates are ineffective. To examine the case with the control qubits in a \
general state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    TemplateBox[{
      SubscriptBox["x", "1"]},
     "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
    TemplateBox[{
      SubscriptBox["x", "2"]},
     "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", "\[CenterEllipsis]", "\[CircleTimes]", 
    TemplateBox[{
      SubscriptBox["x", "n"]},
     "Ket"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "650b6f6a-2b6f-4824-9bcc-b57c2618dad9"],
 ", note that the gates on the target qubit are effective under the \
conditions specified in terms of the bit values at the bottom of the above \
diagram (see also the ",
 ButtonBox["conditional-unitary gates",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/TwoQubitGates#1379525988"],
 "). The conditions are systematically fulfilled by following the Gray code \
sequence, an arrange of bits such that two successive values differ in only \
one bit, the bit strings of which are indicated at the top of the diagram. \
The identity for the bitwise AND,"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1713272112,ExpressionUUID->"3320b68e-aae0-4f32-a76c-314444bcc42d"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox["2", 
      RowBox[{"n", "-", "1"}]], 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox["x", "1"], 
       SubscriptBox["x", "2"], 
       SubscriptBox["\[CenterEllipsis]x", "n"]}], ")"}]}], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
       SubscriptBox["k", "1"]], 
      SubscriptBox["x", 
       SubscriptBox["k", "1"]]}], "-", 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
       RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox["k", "1"], "<", 
        SubscriptBox["k", "2"]}]], 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox["x", 
         SubscriptBox["k", "1"]], "\[CirclePlus]", 
        SubscriptBox["x", 
         SubscriptBox["k", "2"]]}], ")"}]}], "+", 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
       RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox["k", "1"], "<", 
        SubscriptBox["k", "2"], "<", 
        SubscriptBox["k", "3"]}]], 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox["x", 
         SubscriptBox["k", "1"]], "\[CirclePlus]", 
        SubscriptBox["x", 
         SubscriptBox["k", "2"]], "\[CirclePlus]", 
        SubscriptBox["x", 
         SubscriptBox["k", "3"]]}], ")"}]}], "-", "\[CenterEllipsis]", "+", 
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox[
       RowBox[{"(", 
        RowBox[{"-", "1"}], ")"}], 
       RowBox[{"n", "-", "1"}]], 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox["x", "1"], "\[CirclePlus]", 
        SubscriptBox["x", "2"], "\[CirclePlus]", "\[CenterEllipsis]", "\[CirclePlus]", 
        SubscriptBox["x", "n"]}], ")"}]}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"8b646c1b-a18a-43f9-bd0c-26068f4384ba"],
 " ,"
}], "TechNoteText",
 PageWidth->DirectedInfinity[1],
 CellID->501845290,ExpressionUUID->"bcce2246-c8bc-425a-8561-3f5fdd400aa1"],

Cell["\<\
ensures that the above quantum circuit on the right-hand side reproduces the \
desired multi-control unitary gate on the left-hand side.\
\>", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1345507261,ExpressionUUID->"698d7a2a-77c8-497a-83d2-4c351c17d41e"],

